Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo and his Deputy, Mr. Philip Shaibu, will on March 15 take the COVID-19 AstraZeneca vaccine, to mark the rollout of coronavirus vaccination in the state. Mrs Irene Uabor, the Health Educator of Edo State Primary Healthcare Development Board, disclosed this while addressing journalists on Thursday in Benin. Uabor said that the state received 81,080 doses of vaccine meant for about 40,000 persons in the the state on Wednesday night. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! “The state has taken delivery of the AstraZeneca vaccine and will commence vaccination from the 15th of March, 2021. “Gov. Godwin Obaseki and his wife, Betsy, will receive their first jabs on that day as well as the Deputy Governor, Mr Philip Shaibu and his wife. You Are Under Baale Sasa, Olubadan Tells Seriki Sasa Makinde Appoints Aides On Infrastructure, Legal Matters “Also, the Chief Judge of the state, Justice Esther Edigin and her husband are to take the vaccine. “The plan for the rollout is that the health workers in the state will be prioritised. “Those working in isolation centres at the Stella Obasanjo Hospital, Irrua Specialist Teaching Hospital and the University of Benin Teaching Hospital, will get the vaccine because of their exposure to the virus,” she said. Uabor noted that about 22 persons were billed to take the vaccine, after which frontline workers, especially those working in isolation and treatment centres, would get their jabs. Source (NAN)